A RESOLUTION
1 Urging the General Assembly to enact the Workplace Safety and Heat Protection Act
2 (LC 46 0977) to safeguard workers from extreme heat conditions that endanger their health
3 and economic security; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, Georgia workers, particularly those in the construction, manufacturing,
5 agriculture, transportation, and warehousing sectors, are increasingly exposed to extreme
6 heat conditions due to rising temperatures and required outdoor exposure; and
7 WHEREAS, prolonged exposure to high temperatures has been linked to serious health risks,
8 including heat exhaustion, heat stroke, cardiovascular strain, and even fatality,
9 disproportionately impacting workers in physically demanding jobs; and
10 WHEREAS, the current lack of enforceable workplace heat protection standards exacerbates
11 economic vulnerabilities, as work absences due to heat related illness result in loss of wages,
12 financial instability, and increased healthcare costs for workers and their families; and
13 WHEREAS, according to economic studies, workplace injuries and illnesses from extreme
14 heat result in significant productivity losses, increased workers' compensation claims, and
